Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

List of related resources BetaGroupsResponse

400

Parameter error(s) ErrorResponse

403

Forbidden error ErrorResponse

404

Not found error ErrorResponse
Up 
get /v1/apps/{id}/betaLicenseAgreement
(appsBetaLicenseAgreementGetToOneRelated)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[betaLicenseAgreements] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaLicenseAgreements default: null

Return type

BetaLicenseAgreementResponse

get /v1/apps/{id}/prices
(appsPricesGetToManyRelated)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[appPrices] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type appPrices default: null
fields[appPriceTiers] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type appPriceTiers default: null
fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null
limit (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum resources per page default: null
include (optional)
Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null

Return type

AppPricesResponse

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

List of BetaAppReviewDetails BetaAppReviewDetailsResponse

400

Parameter error(s) ErrorResponse

403

Forbidden error ErrorResponse
Up 
get /v1/betaAppReviewDetails/{id}
(betaAppReviewDetailsGetInstance)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[betaAppReviewDetails] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaAppReviewDetails default: null
include (optional)
Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null
fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null

Return type

BetaAppReviewDetailResponse

Forbidden error ErrorResponse
Up 
get /v1/betaGroups/{id}
(betaGroupsGetInstance)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[betaGroups] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaGroups default: null
include (optional)
Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null
fields[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type builds default: null
fields[betaTesters] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaTesters default: null
fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null
limit[betaTesters] (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum number of related betaTesters returned (when they are included) default: null
limit[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum number of related builds returned (when they are included) default: null

Return type

BetaGroupResponse

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Single BetaGroup BetaGroupResponse

400

Parameter error(s) ErrorResponse

403

Forbidden error ErrorResponse

404

Not found error ErrorResponse

409

Request entity error(s) ErrorResponse

BetaLicenseAgreements

Up 
get /v1/betaLicenseAgreements/{id}/app
(betaLicenseAgreementsAppGetToOneRelated)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null

Return type

AppResponse

Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaTesters default: null
limit (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum resources per page default: null

Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null

Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaGroups default: null
fields[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type builds default: null

Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null

Query Parameter — maximum number of related apps returned (when they are included) default: null

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

List of BetaTesters BetaTestersResponse

400

Parameter error(s) ErrorResponse

403

Forbidden error ErrorResponse
Up 
get /v1/betaTesters/{id}
(betaTestersGetInstance)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[betaTesters] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaTesters default: null
include (optional)
Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null
fields[betaGroups] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type betaGroups default: null
fields[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type builds default: null
fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null
limit[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum number of related apps returned (when they are included) default: null
limit[betaGroups] (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum number of related betaGroups returned (when they are included) default: null
limit[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum number of related builds returned (when they are included) default: null

Return type

BetaTesterResponse

Query Parameter — comma-separated list of sort expressions; resources will be sorted as specified default: null
fields[preReleaseVersions] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type preReleaseVersions default: null
limit (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum resources per page default: null
include (optional)
Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null
fields[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type builds default: null
fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null
limit[builds] (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum number of related builds returned (when they are included) default: null

Path parameters

Query parameters

Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type profiles default: null

Query Parameter — comma-separated list of relationships to include default: null

Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type certificates default: null

Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type devices default: null

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Single UserInvitation UserInvitationResponse

400

Parameter error(s) ErrorResponse

403

Forbidden error ErrorResponse

404

Not found error ErrorResponse
Up 
get /v1/userInvitations/{id}/visibleApps
(userInvitationsVisibleAppsGetToManyRelated)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Query parameters

fields[apps] (optional)
Query Parameter — the fields to include for returned resources of type apps default: null
limit (optional)
Query Parameter — maximum resources per page default: null

Return type

AppsResponse

Query Parameter — filter by attribute 'roles' default: null

Query Parameter — filter by attribute 'username' default: null

Produces

This API call produces the following media types according to the Accept request header; the media type will be conveyed by the Content-Type response header.
  • application/json

Responses

200

Single User UserResponse

400

Parameter error(s) ErrorResponse

403

Forbidden error ErrorResponse

404

Not found error ErrorResponse
Up 
patch /v1/users/{id}
(usersUpdateInstance)

Path parameters

id (required)
Path Parameter — the id of the requested resource default: null

Consumes

This API call consumes the following media types via the Content-Type request header:
  • application/json

Request body

UserUpdateRequest UserUpdateRequest (required)
Body Parameter —

Return type

UserResponse
